	dprr:forAssertion <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/443> .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/359> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #359" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Diod. (12.53.1) lists these three, record of whom Livy says Macer and Tubero (see above) also found in early annalists. See note 2." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/358> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #358" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Diod.: {Gr}; Chr. 354 (Capitolino et Cosso); Fast. Hyd. (Capitolino et Carino); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}). Since Cossus was named in Chr. 354 the version in Fast. Cap. may well have been the third possibility above. Degrassi however makes no choice among them (95, 372f.). See Mommsen, RF 2. 222f.; Leuze, Röm. Jahrzählung 269f.; Beloch RG 257f. In CIL 1(2), Index, p. 350, it is suggested that Manlius may also have been a Vulso. On Sulpicius' filiation, see Münzer, RE749." .
